data.content:
In MSTest v4, `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` was removed. The retry/custom-execution extensibility point is now the **`[Retry]` attribute** built into the framework.

**Fix:** Remove your custom `RetryTestMethodAttribute` and use the built-in `[Retry]` attribute instead:

```csharp
using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;

namespace MyApp.Tests;

[TestClass]
public class PaymentServiceTests
{
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(2)]
    public void ProcessPayment_ValidCard_Succeeds()
    {
        Assert.IsTrue(true);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    public void ProcessPayment_ExpiredCard_Fails()
    {
        Assert.IsTrue(true);
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
1. Delete `RetryTestMethodAttribute` entirely — `Execute` is no longer overridable.
2. Use `[TestMethod]` + `[Retry(n)]` (from `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`).

The built-in `[Retry]` attribute re-runs failed tests up to the specified count, matching your original behavior.

